# Atomic camera swap + (optional) mode change on the husarion_camera
# node. Resolves `id` against the current ~/devices list, opens the
# new device, applies the requested mode, publishes new ~/active_device
# + ~/capabilities + ~/active_mode. Audio thread reopens against the
# new device's inferred_audio_device on its next subscribe cycle.
# `camera_info` reloads against the new device's resolved
# `camera_info_url` before the next frame goes out.
#
# Strict-fail contract: any failure (unknown id, V4L2 open error,
# requested mode unsupported on the new camera) leaves the previous
# camera + mode running. The service returns success=false with a
# descriptive `message`; no partial state.

# Composite key matching a CameraDeviceList.devices[].id. For a V4L2
# camera this is its composite id; for a ros_topic source it is the
# topic name. Resolved against ~/devices unless `source_topic` (below)
# is set.
string id

# ROS-topic source (SPEC-ros-topic-source.md). When non-empty, the node
# ignores the local V4L2 device and ingests this external
# sensor_msgs/Image topic through its hardware encoder, even if the
# topic is not (yet) in ~/devices — this is the manual-entry path. Empty
# selects a V4L2 camera (or a discovered topic source) via `id`.
string source_topic

# Mode to apply on the new camera. Each field uses a sentinel "keep
# current" value, inherited from the node's current ~/active_mode:
#   format: "" (empty string)
#   width / height / fps: 0
# If the resolved (format, width, height, fps) tuple is not advertised
# by the new camera's V4L2 enumeration, the service fails — the WebUI
# is expected to surface the error and prompt for a new mode.
string format
uint32 width
uint32 height
float32 fps
---
bool   success
string message
